docs.lead_paragraph: A year ago, even as the Knicks wheeled and darted in glorious flight toward their certain championship, basketball fans glanced sidelong at Low Alcindor hatching out in Milwaukee. The 7-foot-2-inch rookie made mistakes and took punishment, but he led a last-place team to the playoffs. The Knicks had better win it now, people thought, because when Alcindor gets a little more experience and a little more weight. . . .
